    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1652" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αὐδάω</span></b> , impf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αὔδᾱ</span>, ipf. 3 sing. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ηὔδᾱ</span>, aor. iter. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αὐδήσασκε</span>, part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αὐδήσᾱς</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">speak</span> loud and clear, cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αὐδή,
            Στέντορι εἰσαμένη μεγαλήτορι, χαλκεοφώνῳ</span>, | <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὃς τόσον αὐδήσασχ᾽ ὅσον ἄλλοι πεντήκοντα,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 5.786</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> τοῦ
            δὲ Ποσειδά̄ων μεγάλ̓ ἔκλυεν αὐδήσαντος</span>, ‘heard his loud
          boastful utterance,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 4.505</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ὁμοκλήσᾱς ἔπος ηὔδᾱ</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 6.54</span></i>; often w. acc. in the phrase
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀντίον ηὔδᾱ</span>,
          ‘addressed.’</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
